Pakistan
-----
[1] Balochistan, 1 new case
Date: Mon 18 Dec 2017
Source: Geo TV [edited]
https://www.geo.tv/latest/172827-third-polio-case-in-balochistan-reported-from-qilla-abdullah


A 3rd polio case in Balochistan for 2017 was reported on [Mon 18 Dec 2017]. According to officials of the provincial health department, the new case has surfaced from Gulistan tehsil [sub district] of Qilla Abdullah [Killa Abdullah] district in Balochistan.

The virus has been detected in a 16-month-old child in the area. His parents had refused to administer polio drops to him, which is why he contracted the virus, officials said.

The 1st case was reported in July this year [2017] from Chaman area of the same district, Qilla Abdullah. The 2nd case was reported recently from Zhob district of Balochistan.

Qilla Abdullah is considered to be a high-risk area for polio in the province.

A 3-day polio campaign starts in Balochistan today [18 Dec 2017].

The new case has taken the count of polio victims reported in 2017 to 8 from across Pakistan.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[As the last update announcement by WHO, contained in the Global Polio Eradication Initiative weekly update from last week stated, there had been a total of 6 cases of polio confirmed in Pakistan during 2017. The update also announced an early report of a case of polio in Balochistan to be officially counted in this coming week's update. That would bring the total number of reported cases of WPV1 associated disease in Pakistan to 7. That being said, the End Polio Pakistan website lists the national total as 8 with 3 cases reported from Balochistan (see http://www.endpolio.com.pk/polioin-pakistan/polio-cases-in-provinces), supporting this is most likely a newly confirmed/reported case.

According to the information available on the End Polio Pakistan website, there have been 3 cases reported from Balochistan, 2 from Qilla Abdullah district and 1 from Zhob district (http://www.endpolio.com.pk/polioin-pakistan/polio-cases-district-wise-2017).

Maps of Pakistan: http://pakistanmap.facts.co/pakistanmapof/PakistanAdministrativeMap.jpg and https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=5511962,48074.
Balochistan district map: http://lodhran.pk/images/Maps/Balochistan/balochistan-map.jpg. Qilla Abdullah (Killa Abdullah) is located in the northwest of the province and borders with Afghanistan. - Mod.MPP]

******
[2] immunization drive begins
Date: Mon 18 Dec 2017
Source: The Express Tribune [edited]
https://tribune.com.pk/story/1586901/1-countrywide-polio-eradication-drive-begins-today/


Amid stringent security, a 3-day anti-polio campaign has started in selected districts of Punjab, Balochistan, Khyber-Pakhtunkhwa (K-P), and the Federally Administered Tribal Areas (Fata) on [Mon 18 Dec 2017], said Radio Pakistan.

Polio teams will go door-to-door and administer oral polio vaccine drops to children under the age of 5 in 8 districts of Punjab, 20 districts of Balochistan, and 17 districts of K-P and Fata during the immunisation campaign.

In Punjab, nearly 7 million children will be given anti-polio vaccines while in Balochistan more than 1.7 million children and in K-P and Fata, 5 million children will be given polio vaccine drops.

Pakistan is one of just 3 countries in the world, along with Afghanistan and Nigeria that have endemic polio, a once-common childhood virus that can cause paralysis or death. However, immunisation efforts have, in the past, been hampered by militants. In January 2016, a suicide bomber killed 15 people outside a vaccination centre in Quetta in an attack, claimed by the banned Tehreek-e-Taliban Pakistan (TTP) and another militant group, Jundullah. Militants in Pakistan have previously alleged the immunisation campaigns are a cover for Western spies.

Local officials said they had recruited Muslim clerics to promote the immunisations for children after past programmes were met with resistance and even violence by extremists.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
